236. tribuni militares consulari potestate. The Plebeians were trying to get a law passed that the consulship should not be confined to either order, but the Patricians evaded the attempt by changing the constitution. Military tribunes with consular power wcre appointed, and both Patricians and Plebeians were eligible. Until 367, when the office was abolished, there were sometimes consuls, sometimes military tribunes.

239. Sutrinorum urbem. Sutrium, au ancient town of Etruria, faithful to the Romans, and several times besieged by the Etruscans. Camillus retook it on the same day that it had surrendered to the Etruscans.
